ESTOPH Mphela (32) has been sentenced to 15 years imprisonment for killing his girlfriend Kgothatso Pule (27). Mphela was sentenced by the Polokwane High Court in Limpopo on Monday, 30 May. Pule’s body was found buried in the yard of Mphela’s parents’ home at Ga- Setati Village, outside Polokwane, on 2 January 2020. Pule went missing after she had visited Mphela, and a missing persons case was opened and investigated by a provincial task team. Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said after the discovery of the body, the case was changed to murder and was investigated by Sergeant Vivian Gafane. Mphela was later arrested. Mojapelo said the court has imposed a further two years imprisonment for obstructing the course of justice. The sentences will run concurrently. Meanwhile, the Thohoyandou Magistrates Court gave Funani Hlungwani (33) a life sentence on Monday. He was found guilty of stabbing 44-year-old Dankie Ngobeni to death with a knife on 22 August 2020 in Mishiyani Village, outside Giyani. Funani accused Ngobeni who was aged 44 at the time of having an affair with his girlfriend and stealing his clients. . He also accused Ngobeni of taking over his potential clients as they were both builders. “After a heated argument, Hlungwani produced a knife and stabbed Ngobeni who died on the scene,” Mojapelo said. Provincial Police Commissioner Lieutenant-General Thembi Hadebe said: has welcomed the sentences.“This is proof that the rule of law will take its course.” and that those who commit crime will rot in jail,” said Hadebe.